    <Abstract>
      <P.silent><!--**-->
      This document offers a number of demo applets that can be run
      directly from within their documentation. In order to execute
      Mozart Applets, your Web Browser must be Mozart Applet
      enabled. This is done easily, see <Ptr to="appendix.enable">.
    </Abstract>
  
    <Part id="part.constraints">
      <Title/Constraint Applications/
      &chapter.queens;
      &chapter.jobshop;
      &chapter.college;
      &chapter.cutting;
    </Part>

    <Part id="part.concurrent">
      <Title/Multi Agent and Concurrent Applications/
      &chapter.trucks;
      &chapter.bounce;
      &chapter.lift;
      &chapter.transportation;
    </Part>

    <Part id="part.distributed">
      <Title/Distributed Applications/
      &chapter.board;
      &chapter.flights;
      &chapter.corpus;
    </Part>

    <Part id="part.appendix">
       <Title/Appendices/
       &appendix.enable;
    </Part>

